CRQ-002: Implement Responsive Layout

1 Change Request Identification

1.1 CRQ Number: CRQ-002
1.2 Title: Implement Responsive Layout
1.3 Date Raised: 2025-07-27
1.4 Requester: Daniel Zirpoli
1.5 Reviewer: [Assign Reviewer]

2 Purpose

To provide a mobile-friendly, responsive design for the Eleventy-based blog by adding necessary viewport tags, container styles, responsive image rules, and media queries.

3 Scope

Affected Files:
	•	_includes/head.njk
	•	css/styles.css

4 Prerequisites
	1.	Local clone of auto-blogger-repo on branch main
	2.	Node.js and npm installed
	3.	Eleventy installed (npm install @11ty/eleventy --save-dev)
	4.	Backup of existing _includes/head.njk and css/styles.css

5 Change Details

Section	File	Change Description
5.1	_includes/head.njk	Insert <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
5.2	css/styles.css	Add .container { max-width: 800px; margin:0 auto; padding:1rem; }
5.3	css/styles.css	Add img { max-width:100%; height:auto; display:block; margin:1rem 0; }
5.4	css/styles.css	Add @media (max-width:600px) { .container{padding:0.5rem;} h1{font-size:1.5rem;} }

6 Implementation Plan

6.1 Create a feature branch:

git checkout -b feature/responsive-layout main

6.2 Edit _includes/head.njk: add viewport meta tag inside <head>.
6.3 Edit css/styles.css: copy and paste container, image, and media query rules.
6.4 Build locally:

npm run dev  # or npx eleventy --serve

6.5 Verify responsive behavior in browser and on mobile emulator.
6.6 Commit changes:

git add _includes/head.njk css/styles.css
git commit -m "CRQ-002: Add responsive layout support"

6.7 Push branch and open PR against main, referencing CRQ-002.

7 Testing Plan

7.1 Functional: Confirm container width adapts between desktop and mobile.
7.2 Visual: Ensure images do not overflow viewport.
7.3 Regression: Verify no layout issues on existing pages.

8 Deployment Plan

8.1 Merge approved PR into main.
8.2 CI/CD pipeline automatically triggers Eleventy build and deploy.
8.3 Confirm live site shows responsive design.

9 Backout Plan

9.1 If issues arise, revert merge commit:

git revert <merge-commit-SHA>
git push origin main

9.2 CI/CD redeploys last stable version.

10 Impact Analysis

10.1 Performance: Minimal CSS additions—negligible impact.
10.2 User Experience: Significant improvement on mobile readability.

End of CRQ-002